page.title: 09WALKS
page.content: There is a walk in Burwash that I go on quite often, it starts at the Bear Car Park. You need to walk through the car park to get to the field, this field leads to another and usually there are cows grazing here. Then you walk through some corn and every time I go on this walk the corn field is different, it is either thick with corn or it has been ploughed and has deep furrows or it is just a muddy mess and then by a certain stile there is always slushy mud just where you need to put your feet to climb over. I like this muddy walk.
